BUG When using "javac -cp <arg_1> <arg_2>" to compile java codes using the 
    stdlib.jar file, the compiler could not find the package. I had trid

    //codebegin
        import stdlib;
        // or put it into a sub-directory "lib"
        import lib.stdlib;
    //codeend

    Somebody in StackFlow said that stdlib.jar is not a package. Though I did 
    not import it in the class, other errors still occurred during compiling.

SOL It turned out that I have to do "javac -cp .;stdlib.jar test.java" - notice 
    the ".;".

    To run the executable file, I have to specify the classpth again:
    "java -cp .;stdlib.jar SortArray".
    
